---
const steps = [
  { word: 'Define', body: 'Start with the problem, not the solution. We ask diagnostic questions before recommending anything. Triangulate stakeholder input, organizational constraints, and learner needs.' },
  { word: 'Design', body: 'Map the learning paths, the activities, and the assessments. Get alignment from client and SMEs before any production starts.' },
  { word: 'Develop', body: 'Build the training. Maintain accessibility, brand, and pedagogical integrity throughout. Test against the design decisions.' },
  { word: 'Drive', body: 'Deploy and pilot. Train trainers if applicable. Help client teams get learners using it.' },
  { word: 'Determine', body: 'Measure what happened. Report back honestly. Adjust the training, rollout, or strategy based on what the data shows.' },
];
---
<section id="methodology" class="bg-white">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 py-20">
    <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4 text-center">How we work: the 5D Spiral</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto text-center mb-12 leading-relaxed">
      A structured, iterative methodology adapted from ADDIE. The 5D Spiral treats analysis and evaluation as continuous activities rather than discrete phases, and it shapes every engagement we take on.
    </p>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-5 gap-4">
      {steps.map(step => (
        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5">
          <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-slate-300 mb-2">D</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">{step.word}</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">{step.body}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
